---
import Base from '../layouts/base.astro';
import LegalText from '../components/blocks/LegalText.astro';

const body = `
<p class="text-[13px] text-ink-3">Last updated: 4 May 2026 &middot; Effective: 4 May 2026</p>

<h2>1. Agreement</h2>
<p>
  By creating an account or using Beebeeb you agree to these Terms of Service
  ("Terms"). The service is provided by <strong>Initlabs B.V.</strong>,
  Kelvinstraat 34A, 6601 HE Wijchen, Netherlands (KvK 95157565).
</p>

<h2>2. The service</h2>
<p>
  Beebeeb provides end-to-end encrypted cloud storage. Your files are
  encrypted on your device before upload using keys derived from your
  password. We cannot access your file content, names, or metadata beyond
  what is described in our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
</p>
<p>
  We aim for high availability but do not guarantee uninterrupted access.
  We publish real-time status at
  <a href="/status">beebeeb.io/status</a>.
</p>

<h2>3. Your account</h2>
<ul>
  <li>You must be 16 or older to use Beebeeb (GDPR minimum age, Netherlands).</li>
  <li>You are responsible for keeping your credentials secure. We cannot recover
  your encryption key if lost — use the backup phrase shown during onboarding.</li>
  <li>One account per person for Free and Personal plans.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
<p>You may not use Beebeeb to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Store, transmit, or share content that is illegal under Netherlands or EU law.</li>
  <li>Distribute malware, ransomware, or other malicious software.</li>
  <li>Attempt to circumvent our security measures or access other users' data.</li>
  <li>Abuse free resources (e.g. creating multiple Free accounts to avoid storage limits).</li>
  <li>Use our service for automated bulk storage without a commercial agreement.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Violations may result in immediate account suspension. We will attempt to
  notify you before taking action unless doing so creates a security risk.
</p>

<h2>5. Your content</h2>
<p>
  You retain full ownership of all files you store in Beebeeb. Our zero-knowledge
  architecture means we cannot view your content. We do not claim any licence
  over your files beyond the technical rights necessary to store and retrieve
  them on your behalf.
</p>

<h2>6. Payment and refunds</h2>
<p>
  Paid plans are billed monthly or annually in advance. Prices are shown in EUR
  inclusive of applicable VAT. Refunds for unused periods are at our discretion;
  we aim to handle all requests fairly. Payment is processed by Stripe.
</p>

<h2>7. Service modifications and termination</h2>
<p>
  We reserve the right to modify or discontinue the service with 90 days' notice
  for material changes that affect existing paid subscribers, or 30 days for all
  other users. In the event of discontinuation we will provide a data export tool
  for at least 60 days.
</p>
<p>
  You may delete your account at any time from account settings. Deletion is
  permanent and irreversible within 30 days.
</p>

<h2>8. Liability</h2>
<p>
  To the extent permitted by applicable law, Initlabs B.V. is not liable for
  indirect, consequential, or special damages arising from use of the service.
  Our total liability is limited to the fees you paid in the 12 months before
  the claim arose.
</p>
<p>
  Nothing in these Terms limits our liability for death or personal injury caused
  by our negligence, fraud, or any other liability that cannot be excluded by law.
</p>

<h2>9. Governing law and disputes</h2>
<p>
  These Terms are governed by Netherlands law. Disputes that cannot be resolved
  amicably will be submitted to the exclusive jurisdiction of the competent court
  in Arnhem, Netherlands.
</p>

<h2>10. Contact</h2>
<p>
  For questions about these Terms, contact us at
  <a href="mailto:hello@beebeeb.io">hello@beebeeb.io</a>.
</p>
`;
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service — Beebeeb"
  description="Beebeeb terms of service: acceptable use, account rules, liability, and governing law."
  path="/terms"
>
  <!-- Draft banner -->
  <div class="bg-amber-bg border-b border-amber/40 px-8 py-3 text-center text-[13px]" style="color: var(--color-amber-deep);">
    <strong>DRAFT</strong> — Under legal review. Not yet in effect.
  </div>

  <LegalText title="Terms of Service" body={body} />
</Base>
